faqs.question: What is the eligibility criteria for Engineering courses under CENTAC?
faqs.label: What is the eligibility criteria for Engineering courses under CENTAC?

answer.text: Candidates should have passed the Higher Secondary Academic examination conducted by Board of Higher Secondary Examination of Tamil Nadu or other equivalent examination. A minimum of 45% marks for general and 40 % from OBC / MBC / BCM / EBC / BT / SC candidates is required. Also candidate should have done the prescribed subjects, of mathematics, physics and one of the following optional subjects, Chemistry / Bio technology / Computer Science / Bology ( Botany and Zoology) for the candidates of Tamil Nadu. For candidates belonging to other state will need JEE main score for admission.

faqs.question: What are the documents to be attached to carry out the enrolment?
faqs.label: What are the documents to be attached to carry out the enrolment?

answer.text:
Candidates have to attach the following documents with the printout of the application form:
10th or equivalent exam mark sheet
12th or equivalent exam mark sheet
Age proof (Birth Certificate or SSLC marksheet
Copy of Online Payment
Nationality Certificate
Residence Certificate
Permanent Integrated Certificate
Special Category Certificate (if applicable)
Community Certificate (if applicable)
Nativity Certificate (if applicable)

The purpose of this accreditation is to promote and recognize excellence in technical education in colleges – at both undergraduate and post graduate levels. It is a process of quality assurance and improvement, whereby a program in an approved Institution is critically appraised to verify that the Institution or the program continues to meet and/or exceed the Norms and Standards prescribed by regulator from time to time. Institution, Students, employers, and the public at large obtain benefits through the standardized assessment process of NBA about the qualities of the various program offered in the institute.
